        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The date and time picker control (<bpt id="p1">[</bpt>CDateTimeCtrl<ept id="p1">](../mfc/reference/cdatetimectrl-class.md)</ept>) implements an intuitive and recognizable method of entering or selecting a specific date.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The main interface of the control is similar in functionality to a combo box.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>However, if the user expands the control, a month calendar control appears (by default), allowing the user to specify a particular date.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>When a date is chosen, the month calendar control automatically disappears.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>To use both the <bpt id="p1">**</bpt>CDateTimePicker<ept id="p1">**</ept> and <ph id="ph1">`CMonthCalCtrl`</ph> classes in your project, you must include AFXDTCTL.H, usually in your project's STDAFX.H file.</source>
